Distribution. This is one of the species in the group with a wider distribution, ranging from the southern half of Mexico (particularly in the Caribbean domain) to Venezuela , through Guatemala , Belize , Honduras , El Salvador , Nicaragua , Costa Rica , Panama and Colombia (
Fig. 10
). It is one of the three species in this evolutionary lineage that possibly reached the Caribbean NW South American region from its main distribution in the Caribbean Mesoamerican domain in recent times (Montelongo & Gómez-Zurita, 2014 ).

